I didn't use a virus-scanner yet..since TvTeam is VIP. (which you do not get when frakin' around) But I was a bit reticent to execute anything after extraction. I kept wondering "why archive an archive and make it bigger than the original archive?"..was a bit confusing..
But the software works great and everything seems oke.

So, my gratitude to TvTeam.


SQLyog is a good tool for importing/exporting extremely large MySQL databases when you don't have direct MySQL access. Access can be done using a HTTP/PHP tunnel.
Installed three times now, all three on Windows XP, after a day of use when I start the program again it says "The trial version has expired". Did anybody else have this problem?
Avast reports the Keygen as a virus, I would be wary of this release.
